-- ============================================================================
-- BRIDGE FRAMEWORK — REAL ESTATE & PRIVATE ASSETS
-- DDL ported to Databricks SQL (Unity Catalog, Delta Lake)
--
-- Run on a Free-Edition serverless SQL Warehouse.
-- Idempotent: safe to re-run (uses CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS).
--
-- Translation notes vs original T-SQL:
--   * Identity columns: BIGINT GENERATED BY DEFAULT AS IDENTITY (Databricks
--     identity columns must be BIGINT; semantics match SQL Server IDENTITY).
--   * Filtered indexes (`INDEX ix_x WHERE is_current = 1`) replaced with
--     Liquid Clustering on the same predicate columns. Delta auto-OPTIMIZE
--     handles file layout; PK/FK declarations are informational only.
--   * BIT → BOOLEAN, DATETIME2 → TIMESTAMP, NVARCHAR(MAX)/UNIQUEIDENTIFIER → STRING.
--   * Defaults: GETUTCDATE() → current_timestamp(); SYSTEM_USER → current_user().
--   * Row tracking and CDF enabled on all tables that may source MVs later.
--
-- Free Edition limitation:
--   * UNIQUE table constraints (informational, NOT ENFORCED) require
--     'spark.databricks.sql.dsv2.unique.enabled = true', which is disabled on
--     Free Edition. They're commented out below; uncomment on a paid workspace
--     where the flag is set. They're metadata only — uniqueness is not enforced
--     either way; application code remains responsible.
--   * Column DEFAULT values require the Delta table feature
--     'allowColumnDefaults' to be explicitly enabled. Set as a TBLPROPERTY on
--     every table that uses DEFAULT clauses (every table here does).
--   * Liquid Clustering does not support data skipping on BOOLEAN columns.
--     Originally is_current was included in CLUSTER BY for SCD2 query
--     optimization; it has been removed. Filtering on is_current = TRUE still
--     works correctly — Delta just won't prune files based on it. The other
--     clustering columns (enterprise_xxx_id, source_key, etc.) carry the
--     skipping load.
--   * Non-deterministic expressions (uuid(), rand(), random()) cannot be used
--     as column DEFAULTs in Delta. The execution_guid column on
--     bridge.execution_log was originally `DEFAULT uuid()` (NEWID() in T-SQL);
--     callers must now pass uuid() explicitly on INSERT.
-- ============================================================================

USE CATALOG workspace;

CREATE SCHEMA IF NOT EXISTS bridge;
CREATE SCHEMA IF NOT EXISTS dim;
CREATE SCHEMA IF NOT EXISTS fact;

-- ============================================================================
-- HELPER: Drop tables in correct order for clean rebuilds (development only)
-- Uncomment during development if you need to rebuild from scratch.
-- ============================================================================
